            "1: # Git AI Standard v4.0.0 — Differences from v3.0.0",
            "2: ",
            "3: This document describes only what changed between v3.0.0 and v4.0.0. For unchanged sections (Attestation Section format, History Rewriting core behaviors, Notes Reference), refer to the [v3.0.0 specification](git_ai_standard_v3.0.0.md).",
            "4: ",
            "5: ---",
            "6: ",
            "7: ## 1. Schema Version",
            "8: ",
            "9: **v3.0.0:**",
            "10: ```",
            "11: auth********.0.0",
            "12: ```",
            "13: ",
            "14: **v4.0.0:**",
            "15: ```",
            "16: auth********.0.0",
            "17: ```",
            "18: ",
            "19: ### Version Check Loosened",
            "20: ",
            "21: v3.0.0 required an exact match against the `schema_version` constant. v4.0.0 changes this to accept any version starting with `\"authorship/\"`, so implementations can read both v3.x and v4.x notes. This is a one-way upgrade: old v3 implementations cannot read v4 notes, but v4 implementations can read v3 notes.",
            "22: ",
            "23: ---",
            "24: ",
            "25: ## 2. Metadata Section — New Optional Field",
            "26: ",
            "27: The `AuthorshipMetadata` object gains one new optional field:",
            "28: ",
            "29: | Field | Type | Description |",
            "30: |-------|------|-------------|",
            "31: | `change_history` | `array` or `null` | Ordered list of `ChangeHistoryEntry` objects recording every checkpoint (human and AI) that occurred between the parent commit and this commit. Omitted from JSON when `null`/absent. |",
            "32: ",
            "33: ---",
            "34: ",
            "35: ## 3. Prompt Record — New Fields",
            "36: ",
            "37: Two new optional fields on `PromptRecord`:",
            "38: ",
            "39: | Field | Type | Description |",
            "40: |-------|------|-------------|",
            "41: | `cursor_subagents` | `array` of strings | Conversation IDs for Cursor subagent sessions spawned by this conversation. Omitted when absent/empty. |",
            "42: | (context conversations) | *(behavioral)* | Prompt records MAY now represent zero-code-change conversations (planning, Q&A). Identified by all stats fields being `0`. |",
            "43: ",
            "44: ### Context Conversations (New Concept)",
            "45: ",
            "46: v3.0.0 only stored prompt records for conversations that produced code changes. v4.0.0 adds \"context conversations\" — planning, research, and Q&A sessions that occurred between commits but made no code changes. These are collected from the IDE's conversation database and inserted into the `prompts` map with zero stats. Requirements:",
            "47: ",
            "48: - MUST have `human_author` populated.",
            "49: - MUST be scoped to the current workspace (unrelated workspaces excluded).",
            "50: - Identified by `total_additions == 0 && total_deletions == 0 && accepted_lines == 0 && overriden_lines == 0`.",
            "51: ",
            "52: ---",
            "53: ",
            "54: ## 4. Message Object — New Fields and Types",
            "55: ",
            "56: ### New field: `id`",
            "57: ",
            "58: Every `Message` variant (`User`, `Assistant`, `Thinking`, `Plan`, `ToolUse`) gains:",
            "59: ",
            "60: | Field | Type | Description |",
            "61: |-------|------|-------------|",
            "62: | `id` | string or null | Unique message identifier from the IDE (e.g., Cursor `bubble_id`). Used for cross-referencing with IDE-native conversation data and prompt_id backfilling. Omitted when absent. |",
            "63: ",
            "64: ",
            "65: ---",
            "66: ",
            "67: ## 5. Checkpoint Behavior Changes",
            "68: ",
            "69: ### Human changes no longer skipped",
            "70: ",
            "71: **v3.0.0:** Pre-commit checkpoints exited early if there were no AI edits (`has_no_ai_edits && !has_initial_attributions` returned `Ok(None)`).",
            "72: ",
            "73: **v4.0.0:** That early exit is removed. Pre-commit always runs, recording human changes with line stats and line change ranges even when there are no AI attributions. Human-only file entries are kept with empty attributions but populated line data.",
            "74: ",
            "75: ### Deleted files re-included",
            "76: ",
            "77: **v3.0.0:** `get_all_tracked_files()` only listed files currently on disk.",
            "78: ",
            "79: **v4.0.0:** Files from previous checkpoints that no longer exist on disk are re-included so deletion events appear in the change history.",
            "80: ",
            "81: ---",
            "82: ",
            "83: ## 6. Change History (Entirely New)",
            "84: ",
            "85: The core new data structure. A chronological array of `ChangeHistoryEntry` objects stored in `metadata.change_history`, recording every checkpoint between parent commit and this commit.",
            "86: ",
            "87: Note that it records all changes between the timestamps of the parent commit and the current commit, regardless of whether those changes were committed. ",
            "88: ",
            "89: ### ChangeHistoryEntry",
            "90: ",
            "91: | Field | Type | Required | Description |",
            "92: |-------|------|----------|-------------|",
            "93: | `timestamp` | integer | REQUIRED | Unix epoch seconds |",
            "94: | `kind` | string | REQUIRED | `\"human\"`, `\"ai_agent\"`, or `\"ai_tab\"` |",
            "95: | `conversation_id` | string | OPTIONAL | SHA-256 hash of agent ID, linking to `prompts` map |",
            "96: | `agent_type` | string | OPTIONAL | AI tool name (e.g., `\"cursor\"`, `\"claude_code\"`) |",
            "97: | `prompt_id` | string | OPTIONAL | IDE-specific message identifier (e.g., Cursor `bubble_id`) |",
            "98: | `model` | string | OPTIONAL | AI model used |",
            "99: | `prompt_text` | string | OPTIONAL | Actual user prompt text |",
            "100: | `files` | object | REQUIRED | Map of file paths to `FileChangeDetail` |",
            "101: | `line_stats` | object | REQUIRED | Aggregate `CheckpointLineStats` |",
            "102: ",
            "103: ### FileChangeDetail",
            "104: ",
            "105: | Field | Type | Required | Description |",
            "106: |-------|------|----------|-------------|",
            "107: | `added_lines` | array of strings | REQUIRED | Compact range format (`\"n\"` or `\"n-m\"`), new-content coordinates |",
            "108: | `deleted_lines` | array of strings | REQUIRED | Compact range format, old-content coordinates |",
            "109: | `added_line_contents` | array of strings | OPTIONAL | `\"N: <text>\"` format, actual added line content |",
            "110: | `deleted_line_contents` | array of strings | OPTIONAL | `\"N: <text>\"` format, actual deleted line content |",
            "111: ",
            "112: Contiguous single-line changes SHOULD be merged into ranges.",
            "113: ",
            "114: ### CheckpointLineStats",
            "115: ",
            "116: | Field | Type | Default |",
            "117: |-------|------|---------|",
            "118: | `additions` | integer | `0` |",
            "119: | `deletions` | integer | `0` |",
            "120: | `additions_sloc` | integer | `0` |",
            "121: | `deletions_sloc` | integer | `0` |",
            "122: ",
            "123: ### Prompt text resolution strategy",
            "124: ",
            "125: 1. Look up user message matching `prompt_id` in the transcript.",
            "126: 2. Fall back to last user message with timestamp <= checkpoint timestamp.",
            "127: 3. Build a `conv_transcripts` map so earlier checkpoints in the same conversation can resolve prompt text even when the transcript is only attached to the last checkpoint.",
            "128: ",
            "129: ### Prompt ID backfilling",
            "130: ",
            "131: v3.0.0 only backfilled `prompt_id` for the last checkpoint per conversation. v4.0.0 builds a full user message timeline from the latest transcript and backfills ALL checkpoints by assigning the last user message whose timestamp <= checkpoint timestamp.",
            "132: ",
            "133: ### Example",
            "134: ",
            "135: ```json",
            "136: {",
            "137:   \"change_history\": [",
            "138:     {",
            "139:       \"timestamp\": 1712000100,",
            "140:       \"kind\": \"ai_agent\",",
